He's been employed here as a guard
for about a year.

45
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:35,394
He lost his legs in Afghanistan.
He was in Raben's unit.

46
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:38,597
He may have been burned alive.
Is that a car tyre? - Yes

47
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:41,638
I've got to make a call.

48
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:47,879
No image recognition?
We're checking that now

49
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,873
Everything points to the same perpetrator.

50
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:55,989
It would have been nice to get
a briefing before the press conference.

51
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:02,789
Lund knows nothing.
We came out here and then ...

52
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,559
I should have known.

53
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:39,149
I should have...

54
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:45,152
I should have done something.

55
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:53,509
If we'd arrived half an hour sooner.
Just a quarter hour.

56
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:01,918
Lund...
I'm okay.

57
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:12,590
The tyre around the neck is favoured 
against informants in South Africa.

58
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:16,514
